    • Method Detail

      • getRecapCounts

        java.lang.Long[][] getRecapCounts(@NotNull
                                  UserContext inUserContext,
                                  @NotNull
                                  MessageCollector inOutMessageCollector,
                                  @NotNull
                                  DomainQuery inDomainQuery,
                                  @NotNull
                                  RecapContext inRecapContext,
                                  @NotNull
                                  java.util.List<java.lang.Object> inOutHorizontalValues,
                                  @NotNull
                                  java.util.List<java.lang.Object> inOutVerticalValues)
        Return a 2x2 array of columns of array of row values. That is, the format is below [[column_1], [column_2], ...] where column_n = [row_1_value, row_2_value, ...], where row_n_value is the [column, row] integer value, where column numbering is in the horizontal direction and row numbering is in the vertical direction. The cell value in 2x2 array contains the count of the domain query filtered by the X horizontal and y vertical attribute values. The given inOutHorizontalValues and inOutVerticalValues will be trimmed when rows and columns have all zeros.
        Parameters:
        inUserContext - user context
        inOutMessageCollector - error report
        inDomainQuery - the main domain query for the recap, iterated with inOutHorizontalValues and inOutVerticalValues
        inRecapContext - recap context
        inOutHorizontalValues - list of possible values for inHorizontalFieldId Can be trimmed on return for zero values for all columns
        inOutVerticalValues - list of possible values for inVerticalFieldId. Can be trimmed on return for zero values for all rows
        Returns:
        arrays of columns of rows

        inDomainQuery - the main domain query for the recap, iterated with inOutHorizontalValues and inOutVerticalValues
        inRecapContext - recap context

        inVerticalValues - list of all values for inVerticalFieldId.
        Returns:

      • getRecapSumCounts

        java.lang.Double[][] getRecapSumCounts(UserContext inUserContext,
                                       MessageCollector inOutMessageCollector,
                                       DomainQuery inDomainQuery,
                                       RecapContext inRecapContext,
                                       MetafieldId inSumField)
        Return a 2x2 array of columns of array of row values. That is, the format is below [[column_1], [column_2], ...] where column_n = [row_1_value, row_2_value, ...], where row_n_value is the [column, row] integer value, where column numbering is in the horizontal direction and row numbering is in the vertical direction. The cell value in 2x2 array contains the sum of inSumField of the domain query filtered by the X horizontal and y vertical attribute values.
        Parameters:
        inUserContext - user context
        inOutMessageCollector - error report
        inDomainQuery - the main domain query for the recap, iterated with inOutHorizontalValues and inOutVerticalValues
        inRecapContext - recap context
        inSumField - the metafield that will be add to the domain query as sum(inSumField)
        Returns:
        2x2 arrays of SUMs
